{
  "title": "Flooring",
  "source": "stardewvalleywiki",
  "sections": [
    {
      "heading": "Introduction",
      "content": "Flooring is an item that can be used to decorate the floor of the farmhouse , cabins , island farmhouse , sheds , and slime hutches . It is available from the catalogue and randomly sold at both Pierre's General Store and JojaMart .\nFlooring is single-use, and does not stack. It covers the whole room it's placed in and can also be placed on hallway floors between rooms."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Flooring Types",
      "content": "These are all the flooring types, listed in the order they appear in the catalogue ."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Sources",
      "content": "- All flooring types are available from the Catalogue .\n- A random one of the first 56 flooring types is sold at Pierre's General Store for data-sort-value=\"200\"> 200g .\n- A random one of the first 40 flooring types is sold at JojaMart for data-sort-value=\"250\"> 250g . If the flooring sold a Pierre's is one of these 40, the one sold at JojaMart will be the same.\n- Some specific flooring types have other sources, as listed in the table below."
    },
    {
      "heading": "References",
      "content": "↑ See Data/Shops.xnb in the game files. ↑ See Data/Shops.xnb in the game files and ItemQueryResolver::RANDOM_ITEMS in the game code. ↑ See Objects/Mannequin::DayUpdate in the game code. Only triggers if the Mannequin doesn't move or change clothes with the farmer. The floor selected is always the floor on which the Mannequin is standing."
    },
    {
      "heading": "History",
      "content": "- 1.0 : Introduced.\n- 1.1 : Made all varieties available for sale from the Catalogue .\n- 1.4 : Added 16 new floorings (#41-56).\n- 1.6 : Added 41 new floorings. Price at Pierre's increased from data-sort-value=\"100\"> 100g to data-sort-value=\"200\"> 200g .\n- 1.6.9 : Fixed bug where Villagers would avoid tiles containing flooring."
    }
  ],
